## 🚨 CAN Transmission Fault Detection

The system also detects communication failures from individual ECUs.

When a node stops transmitting valid CAN frames:

- The Receiver ECU detects the transmission failure.
- A transmission fault flag is generated.
- The dashboard displays the affected ECU.
- Remaining nodes continue publishing telemetry without interruption.

The image below shows a **DS18B20 Transmission Fault (TX Fault)** detected during runtime.

